#If anything is to be done,<BR> do it well,<BR> with energy and devotion;<BR> the renunciate life led heedlessly<BR> just stirs up the dust.|XXII. HELL 313
#Hurtful deeds <BR> are better left undone<BR> as they always lead to remorse.<BR> Harmless deeds are better done <BR> as no regret will follow.|XXII. HELL 314
#As a border city must be careful protected<BR> so guard yourself both within and without; <BR> build your defenses wisely and in time.<BR> If these things are not attended to <BR> at the right moment<BR> great sadness will come.|XXII. HELL 315
#Distorted views <BR> which create feelings of shame <BR> about that which is not shameful,<BR> or indifference <BR> to that which is shameful,<BR> can cause beings to descend into hell.|XXII. HELL 316
